"Rigid, razor-sharp and fast like an escalator running out of control", this was how a journalist described Dog Called Phenix, after seeing them perform in the Melkweg, Amsterdam. The Amsterdam based band - influenced by Arctic Monkeys, Danko Jones, Foo Fighters, Queens of the Stone Age and White Lies - released their debut album "Someone's Gonna Love Me" end 2008. DCP became 3FM Radio’s Serious Talent, finalist of Emerganza Festival and the Amsterdam Popprize and have played many shows in the club circuit. Their highlights so far are; playing as a support act for a sold out Melkweg, on the main stage of the Zwarte Cross Festival, as the final act for the Amsterdam Uitmarkt and at The United Island Festival in Prague. This year the band, in collaboration with Stefan Schmid of Zuco 103, will release new songs and will do a tour across the Netherlands and abroad. DCP is: Guido Vrouwe (basgitaar), Keimpe Bloem (drums) en Robin Verkaik (zang/gitaar). Venues: the Melkweg, Paradiso, P60, Stairway to Heaven, Waerdse Tempel, P3, Merleijn, the Paard, Atlantis, the Gigant, Plein 79, Altstadt, Cul de Sac, Panama, LVC, and more. Festivals: Zwarte Cross, Liberation Day Festival Amsterdam, Uitmarkt, United Island Festival (Czech Republic), Madness, Prilpop, Kultuurkuur Festival, Roparun Benefit concert, and more.

I've changed the direction of this account recently, and in fact the way I make music.  I no longer use a computer for any of my music production.  Instead I have set myself a challenge to spend a year making music entirely with no computer (except for uploading to soundcloud).  All of my tracks that are of the format YEAR-MONTH-DAY are created entirely using a modular synthesizer, a vermona drm1 drum synth, a couple of pieces of elektron kit and a series of old battered drum machines, synths and hacked up pieces of musical oddity.  All of these tracks will be single pass, then the modular patch and setup will be torn down.  If the recording fails or has errors, so be it.  These tracks represent a snap shot of one person having fun with the gear he has around him.  I hope you enjoy it.

Kultur Shock members joke that their new record "IX" symbolizes the nine lives that the band has had over its 18 years of existence. Or may be the nine circles of hell...
Every record for them is a musical representation of their personal experiences, their life on the road (the band has performed over 800 shows by now), and their views about the world through the lyrics of singer Gino Yevdjevich.
The band has chosen a purist approach- every note on the record is played by a human being, no programming has been used at all, with the intent to bring their sound on this release as close to the live sound of the band as possible.
In addition, they have decided to declare a war on the "loudness war"- the tendency of contemporary artists and engineers to amplify recorded material to a point of self- purpose, to the detriment of the musical quality and the listening experience of their audience. 
Recorded by Jack Endino in Seattle in the summer of 2014, the record is scheduled for digital release on November 11, 2014 to be followed by CD and vinyl releases. The band will be on the road with the songs from "IX" and best of their earlier records in February and March 2015.

Nassau is a side project of a thin old italian man - a so called disc jockey since 1984 - happy to return in a quiet 'rotation per minute way' after years of 130's slots; a sort of homecoming to late 70es/early 80es when we driven at 120 while radio stations and early discos played everything from Greg Kihn Band to Chic, early Simple Minds together with Monsoon and Skatt Brothers, Ian Dury, F.lli La Bionda and Kiss. Nassau was heartbroken by Hacienda and Cosmic Disco, and has no relationship with fluo stuff and rush hours. Nassau goes slowly, as when the sun goes down or the tide comes high. A mystical project where Salsa, Balearic Disco, Ambient, Tropicalism, Cosmic Music, Tablas, Trance and Afro Beat collides. Dictionary:
Ad·ver·sar·y (ad-v&(r)-"ser-E)

1. An opponent; an enemy.
2. The Devil; Satan. Often used with the.

[Middle English adversarie, from Latin adversrius, enemy, from adversus, against.]

Thesaurus:
One that opposes another in a battle, contest, controversy, or debate: antagonist, opponent, opposer, opposition, oppositionist, resister.

Wikipedia:
In cryptography, an adversary is a malicious entity whose aim is to prevent the users of the cryptosystem from achieving their goal (primarily privacy, integrity and availability of data). An adversary's efforts might take the form of attempting to discover secret data, corrupting some of the data in the system, spoofing the identity of a message sender or receiver, or forcing system downtime.

Nigel Wright has been creating audio for over 8 years and is known for
his spacious, expansive sound pieces. NW uses his laptop to process guitar and tape loop source sounds, creating dense, tonal drones.

Mainstay of Auckland experimental performance hub 'The Wine Cellar', NW has been involved with a number of festivals in Auckland, such as alt.music (who he also curates for occasionally). Further afield,  he played at Liquid Architecture 2007 in Brisbane and Sydney.

Collaboration with Andrew Scott (Golden Krone, Un Ciego, Metal Rouge) is the mobiustrip Nest. NW also frequently collaborates live with Tim Coster (Plains).

NW has also worked with audio/visual pieces with his first work premiering at the 2006 Auckland International Film Festival, in an audio-visual feedback loop entitled 'Release', based on video work supplied by San Franciso artist Aaron Coyes.

Joseph McGeechan/iFormat/Obsoleet/BCR Boys(One Half)

Joseph McGeechan began his career in 2008 as one half of the BCR Boys they released on their own Backwater Community Recordings label and also on Perc Trax. With further releases on Synewave and Sleaze, 2011 saw them headline both Berlin heavyweights, Tresor and Berghain.

Joseph’s solo productions are uncompromising basic techno, influenced by the sound of early techno on labels like Tresor, Axis, Downwards and newer labels like Repitch, 3TH, Black Sun Records and Inner Surface Music.

iFormat has a darker, more aggressive, industrial sound. Heavily influenced by the sinister and eerie soundscapes of sci-fi and horror movies, these give a disturbing sense of foreboding to McGeechan’s dystopian, post-punk exploration of the decay of society.

Obsoleet is a journey of exploration of the inner self, exploring the boundaries of human emotion. Using dark, industrial, metallic and almost sci-fi sounds, we try and find ways to reconnect, with ourself and those around us, standing on the borderline of uncertainty, looking for escape.

To become obsolete, is to no longer be recognised. It no longer becomes relevant who makes the music, but more what the music is about. In an attempt to no longer be yourself, you choose to assume another identity. Disconnecting from yourself, to become something you are not, as you attempt to escape something you no longer want to be.

His music can be found on labels like: Synewave, Local Sound Network, Perc Trax, Prosthetic Pressings, Djax Upbeats, Sleaze, Monolith Records, Writtentozero, Decoy, Nightmare Factory Records, UFF Records and many more.

His music has been supported by artists like Regis, Ancient Methods, Ryuji Takeuchi, Adam X, Zadig, Dasha Rush, Xhin, Reeko, James Ruskin, Luke Slater, Bas Mooy, D.Carbone, Dave Clarke, Norman Nodge, Rebekah and many more.

He has been remixed by artists like Ancient Methods, Perc, Ryuji Takeuchi, Excluded, Voidloss, Electrorites, Sawf, K209, Go Hiyama, Gary Beck, Mike Humphries, Audio Injection and many more, and has remixed artists like Ryuji Takeuchi, Miss Djax, Patrick DSP, Gary Beck, Monoloc, Hans Bouffmyhre and more.

Joseph has played alongside a wide array of artists like Zadig, Sleeparchive, Davide Carbone, Ascion, Steve Bicknell, J.C, UVB, Max Durante, Damon Wild, Marcel Dettmann, Diego Hostettler, Dave Ellesmere, Norman Nodge, Bas Mooy, Xhin, Rebekah, Hans Bouffmyhre, Billy Nasty, Space Djz, Psyk, Angel Alanis, Patrick Walker (FSG), Erphun, Casual Violence, Bill Youngman, Joey Beltram, Alan Fitzpatrick, The Advent, Slam, Pacou, Violet Poison, Mace, The Horrorist and many more.

He has been a regular guest in Tresor, as well as playing other clubs in Berlin like Liber Null, Suicide Circus, Subland, Berghain, Griessmuehle, and places like Madrid, Prague, Amsterdam, Koln, Moscow, Glasgow, Edinburgh, Aberdeen, Manchester, London, Leeds and Birmingham.

Kapela, ktorá nesie v celku netradičné meno „ajtak“, vznikla, pre niekoho dávno, pre niekoho nedávno. „Skladať“ sa začala už v roku 2004. Na začiatku jej cesty stál Tibo - gitarista a spevák a Vlado - bubeník - samouk, ktorí sa nedali odradiť rozpadom ich predošlej kapely. Naopak, pokúsili sa vytvoriť niečo nové a svieže. Tým sa potvrdilo staré známe „koniec je mnohokrát začiatkom niečoho nového“. V roku 2005 medzi seba (zatiaľ) dvojčlenná kapela pribrala Maťa v podobe basovej posily. Podstatné pre nich bolo, že sa zhodovali. Vo víziách, plánoch, životnom štýle... V čase, kedy sa kapela začala objavovať na pódiách si zostavu všimla Zuzka, ktorá si povedala, že spievať v kapele „ajtak“ by bolo viac než super. Ticho ich podporovala a verila, že ju snáď jedného dňa oslovia a zavolajú medzi seba. I tak sa aj stalo. Legenda hovorí, že prvý mesiac jej účinkovania v kapele a na pódiách nespievala, iba otvárala ústa na mikrofón... Netrvalo dlho a kapela sa rozrástla o jediného zahraničného a zároveň najmladšieho člena „ajtakovskej“ posádky – Andrewa. Talentovaný spevák a sólový gitarista znamenal pre skupinu osvieženie v podobe nápadov a vlastného hudobného štýlu. Doposiaľ poslednou členkou, ktorá do kapely pribudla je Saška, ktorá svojou hrou na klavíri, spevom a talentom tvoriť originálne texty oslovila nejedného poslucháča. V júni 2011 vydala kapela svoj (oficiálne) prvý album s názvom „Aj tak Ťa nenechám“. O 4 roky neskôr „ajtakovci“ vytvorili (oficiálne) druhý album „Všetko“. Spája ich hudba, priateľstvo, spoločné spomienky, ale hlavne ich spája túžba uctievať Ježiša Krista hudbou. O to sa snažia, na tom pracujú a veria, že ich tento sen bude hnať stále vopred.

Hans Tammen creates music that has been described as an alien world of bizarre textures and a journey through the land of unending sonic operations. He produces rapid-fire juxtapositions of radically contrastive and fascinating sounds, with micropolyphonic timbres and textures, aggressive sonic eruptions, but also quiet pulses and barely audible noises - through means of his ENDANGERED GUITAR and interactive software programming, by working with the room itself, and, as a critic observed, with his "...fingers stuck in a high voltage outlet". Signal To Noise called his works "...a killer tour de force of post-everything guitar damage", All Music Guide recommended him: "...clearly one of the best experimental guitarists to come forward during the 1990s."

His numerous projects include site-specific performances and collaborative efforts with dance, light, video, and theatre, utilizing technology from planetarium projectors to guitar robots and disklavier pianos. He received a Fellowship from the New York Foundation of the Arts (NYFA) in the category Digital/Electronic Arts in 2009 for the ENDANGERED GUITAR - a hybrid guitar/software instrument used to control interactive live sound processing. His THIRD EYE ORCHESTRA open form compositions for large ensembles and live sound processing are inspired by Earle Brown's Available Forms, and based on numerous scored "building blocks" that are constantly rearranged when performed.

Check out new album 'Moonshot' now!

Derek grew up in the Washington, D.C. area music scene, he started first playing guitar in several bands throughout junior high and high school in the early 90's, mostly Nirvana covers. Those early influences also included his sister's Prince and Led Zeppelin records, his dad's Fleetwood Mac, ABBA, and 60's surf rock records. The late 90's saw him immersed in the world of improvised rock music and jazz. Not until late into college, pursuing an undergrad in Geography, did the electronic music world envelop him fully, pushing him to buy a set of turntables in 2002. He immersed himself in sounds and was buying records at now shuttered D.C. shops like DJ Hut and Yoshitoshi. Downtempo nights at Eighteenth St. Lounge, legendary Sunday nights at Red with Sam "The Man" Burns, Hippie Torales and other house legends, and the quirky party in a Moroccan restaurant in Alexandria called Lemur Lounge,  all informed his early years of clubbing and record shopping in the early 2000’s. 
A move to Colorado in 2004 saw him really develop his craft,  with weekly residencies in Boulder for a 4 year span, usually playing open to close, sharpening his skills slowly but surely. Then a move to Denver in 2013 brought new opportunities, joining the Family Affair crew, a push into music production, and throwing the occasional party.  Derek is starting 2019 out with a fresh move to Brooklyn, NY, after 14 years of living in Colorado. 2019 will also see his debut release of original material, followed up by a second EP via US label, Make Mistakes.  
Known for his ability to adapt seamlessly to most any type of gig, he's equally comfortable playing lower bpm, eclectic opening sets, to banging out house and techno in a dark basement, to disco and funk party jams on a sunny rooftop.

freesample ist ein online_label für elektronische musik. dabei beschränken wir uns nicht nur auf ein
bestimmtes genre, sondern suchen innovative künstler mit kreativem sound und stil, die unsere
attitüde teilen und mit uns zusammenarbeiten möchten. egal ob techno, drum‘n‘bass, dub etc.
wir releasen ausschließlich musik, die von herzen kommt und das gewisse etwas hat.

_____________________________________________________________________


ausschlaggebend für die gründung von freesample waren die zunehmende kommerzialisierung von
partys und der nervig quälende einheitsbrei von elektronischer tanzmusik. dazu kommen künstlerkult
und ein publikum, dass für unbehagen sorgt. schimpfen ist zu einfach, lustig aber nicht unser ding,
machen ist besser.

sicherlich gibt es dazu keine patentlösung, doch wir versuchen, mit unseren aktionen gleichgesinnte zu
erreichen und eine community aufzubauen, die einfach nur spass macht und hat.

wir machen musik, wie wir sie selbst gern hören und veranstalten parties, wie wir sie selbst feiern
wollen, die es aber leider viel zu selten gibt. nicht gast sondern teil der community zu sein ist wichtig.
günstige getränke und speisen schaffen von vorn herein gleichberechtigung. keine
oder zumindest sehr niedrige eintrittpreise sind teil unseres konzeptes und es gibt musik die von herzen
kommt. all das, und das ist uns sehr wichtig, geschieht ohne gewinnerzielungsabsicht.


“denn sonst ist alles wieder so trist wie kapitalismus im kopf halt ist.“

_____________________________________________________________________


freesample is an online_label offering electronic music for free.
But we're not just stickin' to one special genre, we're looking
for innovative artist with a creative sound and style, who'd like
to coorporate with us. techno, drum'n'bass, dub etc., anyway we
don't mind. we only release music comin' straight from the heart
and having the certain something.



decisive for the founding of freesample was, that we felt parties
growing more and more commercial, in this case effecting the quality of electronic music negatively. in addition artist are somehow hovering above the crowds - celebrating more personality cult and less the party - and the audience makes you uncomfortable in numerous occasions.

but grumbling about these facts is too easy, funny, but not our
style.

actually there's no solution solving all of these problems, but
we're trying to find like-minded people supporting our actions,
to create a community having good mood and fun.

we use to play/produce music, we like to hear and stage parties
we like to celebrate, but which are too rare. important is not
to feel like a guest, but rather to be part of the community.
besides, cheap drinks, food and no (or low) admission charges
give you a feeling of equality and are therefor a firm part of
our concept. All this, an that's pretty important for us, happens
without any intention for benefit.

If you would have cast your eyes over this bio around 5 years ago you would be reading about the highlights of Sean's career thus far. You would be reading examples of Sean supporting artists like Bob Sinclar, David Guetta, Louie Vega & Kenny Dope, DJ Spen, Karizma etc the list goes on.
Today Sean has moved into being an artist defined in his own right. Sean is now one of the only artists in the world to headline for three of the biggest brands in house music Hed Kandi, Soul Heaven and Stereo Sushi. No artist in the world can boast such a repertoire of headline appearances playing under the banner of such huge well-known brands.

A 20+ year veteran of the Canadian west-coast intentional dance scene, Khan's lush sets are filled with tribal rhythms, beautiful melodies and mystical landscapes. He is a master of the live mix, seamlessly blending loops and layers, weaving epic soundscapes on the fly from the raw elements of his carefully selected tracks, while building the energy of the dance floor to its peak. His mission is to facilitate deep, transcendent journeys that bring dancers to a state of higher consciousness, awakening and deepening into the mystery of the dance, and to spread his conscious groove to as many souls as he can reach along the way. From peak sets to early morning transformations to glorious daytime throw-downs, Khan can bring life to any dance floor. Hailing from the Victoria on Canada's west-coast and a summer festival favorite, Khan's infectious spirit is sure to give rise to some serious magic on the dance floor and beyond. 

Dancefloor Endorsements:

"The tasteful blend of organic and electronic sounds, Khan summons from inspiration beyond this world, stimulates the mind and the body producing, in me, what feels to be closer to a spiritual experience than the 'zombie dance' by more common 4/4, Akan drum, loop electronic music." - Aaron Klingbeil

"I was transported into one of the most satisfying spiritual dance experiences in the last 17 years of being involved in the electronic dance movement. An intelligent, perfectly orchestrated sonic journey which engaged every aspect of my being by effortlessly possessing me, bringing me into complete unity with the music and the dance." - Tracey Budy


"Never before had I felt the cohesion of the dance floor, never had I felt so welcomed by music and embraced by its generosity. This was the moment that music festivals all changed for me." - Heath Carra


"Khan's ability to bring a crowd from ground zero to the heights of the heavens is pure magic. It's always a mystical journey from the heart." - Stephanie McColl
 

"While staying true to his progressive house roots, Khan has delved into ethnic beats and tribal sounds. His music has evolved from soothing sounds of vinyl to the sophisticated, layered builds of Ableton Live. His sets are topnotch, each different yet beautiful." - Junaid Ziauddin
 

"Khan brings to the table an energy that is divine in the sounds that he mixes" - Lyle Rhodes
 

To date Khan has ecstatically shared the stage with artists such as, Merkaba, Kalya Scintilla, Bird of Pray, Ill Gates, Infected Mushrooms, Delhi to Dublin, Kaminanda, David Starfire, GOVINDA,  Adham Sheikh and Blue Lunar Monkey.

MC, Productor y gestor cultural del país de su procedencia: Perú. Inició su carrera musical con la fundación del grupo pionero del rap peruano Clan Urbano, con 4 discos publicados, múltiples compilatorios al rededor del mundo, obtuvieron un reconocimiento por la Comunidad Andina de Naciones en el 2010 (Premio a la mejor canción urbana), también se hicieron con el premio de Ganador Absoluto del Certamen musical más importante de su país, 3ra Edición del Festival Claro de la Música 2010.

Técnico en Ingeniería de Sonido, fundó el estudio de grabación La Placa Records, convirtiéndose en uno de los estudios más importantes de la escena Hip Hop del Perú, desde allí impulsa la carrera de los grupos que pasan por sus filas. Ha brindado talleres de Hip Hop en distritos y escuelas más alejadas de la capital, alternando con artistas internacionales en escenarios y colaboraciones; ferviente creyente en el movimiento hip hop de su país, ha apostado por la buena difusión de ésta, a través de su programa Raperground en radio y televisión. Se encuentra actualmente preparando su primer disco en solitario que llevará por título "Sin temor a equivocarme", donde consolida como certera, su decisión de haber elegido el hip hop como forma de vida.

Sinsect is a hard-hitting industrial strength fusion of power-noise, EBM and drum & bass.

Sinsect was spawned by James Ashley in 1997 as DJ Sinsect in the NYC industrial/noise club scene, with residencies at The Pyramid and Z-Bar, and also had guest appearances at Mother & the Bank. As a natural evolution, he started creating his own material, and worked with other noise artists in NYC, New Jersey, and Atlanta.

Drawing inspiration from a myriad of sources has kept the Sinsect sound in constant flux, with every release being a sonic adventure, from the rhythmic noise of "Contained" (2003, out of print), the downtempo dark ambient soundscapes of Hidden Agenda (2004, remastered in 2010) to the harsh power noise beats of Darker Days Ahead (2009).

2010's, "Shadow Wars", is a 3 track maxi-single setting the stage for the next evolution of Sinsect. Hard, fast and fun, "Shadow Wars" is a distorted fusion of darkstep drum & bass and power noise, with plenty of dancefloor energy. Rounding it out are nine bonus remixes from a wide variety of artists from many different musical foundations.

Crunch Pod Records signed Sinsect to release "Bug Life" in early 2011, as well taking over the digital distribution of "Darker Days Ahead" and "Shadow Wars".
Along with several compilation tracks and remixes over the last 2 years, Sinsect is nearing the finish line for the newest album "Broken Heroes"

[astral projects] Records is an independent record label founded by musician/producer Js.One in 2001 from the former Js Productions. Styles of the music released since it’s inception range from hip-hop (Js.One), to acoustic/indie rock, to jazz-funk/fusion, to boogie funk (Nova), to afro-beat funk (The Nubians), to hypnagogic nostalgia (Le Soleil et Les Etoiles), to dirty synth funk/hip-hop (Stony Watson), and a complex combination of each. All recordings are produced by Js.One [astral projects] also features a weekly podcast of obscure and rare records: Vintage Crates, which delves into many styles from mostly the 1960’s-80’s such as funk, jazz, samba, true-school hip-hop, bossa nova, boogie, library, disco, psych, and the avant-garde. From many countries like Italy, Brazil, Mali, France, Angola, Japan, Congo(s), the former Soviet Union, Guinea, and many more.

Beat.imprint members Skye Ashbrook and John Gomi have been creating music and art under the name beat.imprint for over 20 years. They have explored dance music and experimental music with equal intensity, combining styles and eschewing genres. They work with beats, bass, and space with influences ranging from Kraftwerk to John Coltrane by way of My Bloody Valentine meets DJ Screw. Beat Imprint owes as much to hip hop as to drone, creating cinematic musical experiences that make you think as well as make you dance.

Beat.imprint perform with traditional instrumentation and modern electronics. Their shows include original songs and video as well as improvisational elements that have never existed outside of that performance. Beat Imprint fully embrace sound and image to create new immersive experiences.

The existence of Dodd has long been questioned by those who've not been on his dancefloor -- but those who've been there are fast and thorough believers. Zantz´ style is characterized as a creative mix of elements which overlap musical genres; due to the fact that Zantz eludes being cataloged by proposing and exposing the music that stimulates him, always keeping in mind the objective of creating an emotional atmosphere regardless of the place, people, etc. There are no rules in his sets, the goal is putting clubbers on the dance floor while keeping the original, eclectic and persuasive nature of electronic music in mind.
